title: For Sale:  One of a kind custom Mosin Nagant M44
location: Near Robert Rd. and Lakeshore Dr., Prescott Valley, Arizona
postcontent: I know what you are thinking...another Mosin Nagant, but look again. This rifle is unlike any other. A lot of work has gone into this beauty. All pits have been sanded down to a smooth finish and left raw to look like NO other M44. There was over 20 hours put into the barrel and receiver of this rifle to remove pitting. It has been oiled to prevent rusting. I could have had it chromed but I couldn't see spending the money at the time. Custom one of a kind bent bolt and threaded handle that allowed for the Center Point 6x16x40 dual illuminated reticle scope. The scope is mounted to the rail that was tapped and drilled to the receiver with a close tolerance. Also custom soldered to the back of the bolt safety is a weathered skull(not another like it!)Bolt action is one of the smoothest I have seen and the bore on this rifle is excellent. The bayonet lug has been cleanly shaved off and looks like it came that way. I have seen guys customize the 91/30 by cutting the barrel down but I decided to go with the shorter M44 that is already shorter from the factory. The stock M44's are selling around $475 now believe it or not. So if you own one they are worth more now since they stopped importing them a few years ago. The stock this M44 sits in is the ProMag Archangel. The stock has a fully adjustable cheek-riser and length of pull, making it a custom fit to any shooter. This stock also allows for the 10 round magazine which is included. Great shooting rifle but I am trying to fund or trade for an AK platform rifle. I am also throwing in a sling that uses a QD mount in the back of the stock and the original wood stock and bayonet as well. I will sell for $650 or trade for an AK that shoots 7.62x39 no other calibers please. If you are looking for a one of a kind M44, this is it. All it needs is a Timney trigger(around $80) and your done. I think $650 is a more than fair price for this rifle. A stock M44 is around $475 alone right now and the stock is available for around $130. The scope was $60 and the rail was $15 not to mention the labor that has gone into it. postcontent: This is a 12" aluminum rail for an AR-15 with keymod mounting points and a standard 1913 rail running the whole top length. The top is also "t-marked" so that you can re-mount accessories to the same position. This is a copy of the strike industries superfin. I've used a 16" version of this rail for one of my AR builds, and it has held a backup iron sight and sling mount well with no wobble or distortion when I sling up to shoot with it.The rail is held on with 8 small screws that attach to threaded holes in the barrel nut, which it comes with. This is designed to fit over a LOW PROFILE gas block.
